Edition:
Quote: (2.)  Batten and wire fence, at least 3 ft. 9 in. high, of substantial material, firmly erected, with one or more wires, not lighter than No. 8 in steel, or black or galvanised iron; battens either driven securely into the ground and securely stapled, or intertwined in wires in an upright position, and not more than 3 in. apart. <i>Ibid.</i> 19 ... and a good paling fence on ordinary bush land with double No. 8 wires top and bottom, with 1/2 in. palings, and 7 in. posts sunk 2 ft. in the ground, can be erected at about 12s. per chain.
